===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|might|lang=enm}}, {{term|myghte|lang=enm}}, (also {{term|maught|lang=enm}}, {{term|macht|lang=enm}}, {{term|maht|lang=enm}}), from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|miht|lang=ang}}, {{term|mieht|lang=ang}}, {{term|meaht|lang=ang}}, {{term|mæht||might, bodily strength, power, authority, ability, virtue, mighty work, miracle, angel|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*mahtiz}}, {{m|gem-pro|*mahtuz||might, power}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*mógʰtis}}, {{m|ine-pro|*magʰ-||to allow, be able, help}}, corresponding to Germanic {{m|gem-pro|*maganą}} + {{m|gem-pro|*-þiz}}. Cognate with {{etyl|sco|-}} {{term|micht|lang=sco}}, {{term|maucht||might|lang=sco}}, {{etyl|frr|-}} {{term|macht||might, ability|lang=frr}}, {{etyl|fy|-}} {{term|macht||might, ability|lang=fy}}, {{etyl|nl|-}} {{term|macht||might, power|lang=nl}}, {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|Macht||power, might|lang=de}}, {{etyl|sv|-}} {{term|makt||might|lang=sv}}, {{etyl|is|-}} {{term|máttur||might|lang=is}}.

