====Verb====
{{head|en|verb}}

#{{lb|en|auxiliary}} Used to indicate [[conditional]] or [[possible]] [[action]]s.
#:{{ux|en|I '''might''' go to the party, but I haven't decided yet.}}
#*{{RQ:Chmbrs YngrSt|IX}}
#*:“A tight little craft,” was Austin’s invariable comment on the matron;{{nb...}}. &para; Near her wandered her husband, orientally bland, invariably affable, and from time to time squinting sideways, as usual, in the ever-renewed expectation that he '''might''' catch a glimpse of his stiff, retroussé moustache.
#*{{quote-magazine|date=2013-06-07|author=David Simpson
|volume=188|issue=26|page=36|magazine={{w|The Guardian Weekly}}
|title=[http://www.guardian.co.uk/books/2013/may/18/falling-upwards-richard-holmes-review Fantasy of navigation]
|passage=It is tempting to speculate about the incentives or compulsions that '''might''' explain why anyone would take to the skies in [the] basket [of a balloon]: perhaps out of a desire to escape the gravity of this world or to get a preview of the next;{{nb...}}.}}
#{{lb|en|auxiliary}} {{en-simple past of|may}} Used to indicate [[permission]] in past tense.
#:{{ux|en|He asked me if he '''might''' go to the party, but I haven't decided yet.}}
#{{lb|en|auxiliary}} {{en-simple past of|may}} Used to indicate [[possibility]] in past tense.
#:{{ux|en|I thought that I '''might''' go the next day.}}
#*{{quote-book|year=1913|author={{w|Joseph C. Lincoln}}|chapter=1
|title=[http://openlibrary.org/works/OL5535161W Mr. Pratt's Patients]|chapter=1
|passage=I stumbled along through the young pines and huckleberry bushes. Pretty soon I struck into a sort of path that, I cal'lated, '''might''' lead to the road I was hunting for. It twisted and turned, and, the first thing I knew, made a sudden bend around a bunch of bayberry scrub and opened out into a big clear space like a lawn.}}
#*{{quote-book|year=1963|author={{w|Margery Allingham}}|title={{w|The China Governess}}
|chapter=19|url=http://openlibrary.org/works/OL2004261W
|passage=Meanwhile Nanny Broome was recovering from her initial panic and seemed anxious to make up for any kudos she '''might''' have lost, by exerting her personality to the utmost. She took the policeman's helmet and placed it on a chair, and unfolded his tunic to shake it and fold it up again for him.}}

